latestPosts.caption:
🌸 Happy Mother’s Day to All the Incredible Moms! 🌸

Motherhood is a beautiful journey, but it comes with its own set of challenges-especially when it comes to focusing on your own physical health after childbirth.

Did you know that more than 50% of women struggle to prioritize their physical health postpartum? 

The main reasons? Lack of time and support. This often leads to long-term health issues like exhaustion, back pain, spondylitis, and more.

But here’s an important reminder: Your health matters, too. Experts recommend that postpartum women aim for at least 150 minutes of physical activity each week-that’s just 30 minutes a day, five days a week! 

Why Strength Training Matters
Strength training is one of the most critical (yet overlooked) aspects of women’s health, especially in your 30s. It helps build muscle, strengthens bones, and boosts energy levels-but it’s still not widely embraced.
This Mother’s Day, let’s change that.

Let’s make a promise to ourselves and each other: Prioritize your physical health. Just 30 minutes a day can make a world of difference.
You deserve to feel strong, healthy, and empowered-today and every day. 💪🌷

Happy Mother’s Day!
#MothersDay #StrongMoms #PostpartumHealth #WomenWhoLift #SelfCareMatters

latestPosts.caption:
Work shouldn’t feel like a battle on your not-so-great days ❌

Women go through different phases in their lives—physically and mentally—which take time to adjust to and get comfortable with. It could be your first day of periods, a low morning, a sleepless night with your child, or just a normal, random, confusing day!

We understand the need for space—to take a break, breathe for a moment, and return with renewed energy.

So, we did something… 🤠

We introduced the De-Caff Comfort & NO-JUDGEMENT Room—a space exclusively for our women to rest, recharge, or simply take a break from the many things life throws at them. With recliners, hot bags, chocolates, books, and cozy couches, we aimed to bring the feeling of home into the workplace. A place where they can GO & CHILL, without being judged. 🤓

At Pep Brands, every day is about creating a workplace where women feel valued, cared for, and understood 🫂.

To all the powerful women at Pep—this one’s for you! ❤️

And yes—Happy Women’s Day, every day!
